Tracey Community Code of Conduct
-----------------------------------

Purpose
----------

This repository exists to support learning, collaboration, and open-source development.
We welcome students, hobbyists, professionals, and anyone willing to contribute their time, knowledge, skills, ideas, documentation, testing, or development efforts to improve the project and its ecosystem.
Our goal is to create a community where contributors can learn from each other, share knowledge, discuss ideas openly, and work together in a respectful and professional environment.

Expected Behavior
--------------------

All community members are expected to:

- Treat others with respect and professionalism.
- Provide constructive and positive criticism.
- Remain open-minded during discussions and reviews.
- Focus on technical improvement and problem solving.
- Help create a welcoming environment for newcomers.
- Respect different backgrounds, experiences, and skill levels.
- Encourage learning and knowledge sharing.
- Accept feedback gracefully and professionally.

Unacceptable Behavior
------------------------

The following behavior is not permitted within the project community:

- Harassment or abusive conduct.
- Personal attacks or insults.
- Stalking or intimidation.
- Discrimination of any kind.
- Hate speech or offensive content.
- Threats or attempts to harm others.
- Spamming, trolling, or intentionally disrupting discussions.
- Publishing or leaking private or confidential information.
- Impersonating another individual.
- Repeated disruptive behavior after warnings have been issued.
- Any activity that violates applicable laws.

Enforcement
--------------

Project maintainers reserve the right to take action when these guidelines are violated.

Possible actions include:

- 1 Informal warning.
- 2 Temporary restriction of repository privileges.
- 3 Temporary suspension from development activities.
- 4 Limited access to project resources and discussions.
- 5 Permanent removal from the community.
- 6 Permanent ban from project spaces and repositories.

The severity of enforcement will depend on the nature, frequency, and impact of the violation.
Repeated violations may result in increasingly severe consequences.

Legal Compliance
-------------------

This Code of Conduct is intended to operate alongside applicable laws and regulations within the jurisdiction of each community member.

Community members are responsible for complying with the laws of their respective countries and regions.

Where appropriate and legally possible, project maintainers may cooperate with lawful investigations or legal processes relating to serious violations, including harassment, threats, stalking, privacy violations, or other unlawful conduct.

Reporting
------------

If you experience or witness behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please contact the project maintainer.

- Discord: uoctamika (me)
- Email: uoctamika.codeberg.org@gmail.com (me)

All reports will be reviewed in good faith and handled as responsibly as possible.
Retaliation against individuals who report violations in good faith is not permitted.

Final Notes
--------------

By participating in this repository, community space, discussions, issues, pull requests, or related project activities, you agree to follow this Code of Conduct.
Together we can maintain a respectful, welcoming, and productive community for everyone.
